# Frontend Apps

## Scope

Work **only** in `frontend/app/`, `frontend/council-app/`, and `frontend/faculty/`.

**Ignore completely** (redundant, do not search or reference):
`frontend/student/`, `frontend/council/`, `frontend/dean/`

## Active apps

| Folder | Users | Key paths |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| `frontend/app/` | Students | `lib/api.ts`, `app/`, `components/screens/` |
| `frontend/council-app/` | Council | `lib/api.ts`, `app/(dashboard)/`, `contexts/DataContext.tsx` |
| `frontend/faculty/` | Faculty, Principal | `lib/api.ts`, `app/(dashboard)/`, `contexts/DataContext.tsx` |

## Env vars & API base

All three Next.js apps use `NEXT_PUBLIC_SERVER_ADDRESS` → `${SERVER}/api/v1`.

| App | Token keys (localStorage) |
|-----|---------------------------|
| `frontend/app/` | `accessToken`, `refreshToken` |
| `frontend/council-app/` | `council_accessToken`, `council_refreshToken` |
| `frontend/faculty/` | `faculty_accessToken`, `faculty_refreshToken` |

API clients with 401 refresh interceptors:
- `frontend/app/lib/api.ts`
- `frontend/council-app/lib/api.ts`
- `frontend/faculty/lib/api.ts`

## frontend/app (student)

- Browse events, register, teams, tickets, my events, calendar
- Read `frontend/app/AGENTS.md` for Next.js version notes

## frontend/council-app (council)

- Read `frontend/council-app/AGENTS.md` for Next.js version notes
- Event transform + approval chain: `lib/api.ts`
- State controls: `app/(dashboard)/controls/[id]/page.tsx`
- Submit/resubmit: `app/(dashboard)/approvals/page.tsx`

## frontend/faculty (faculty / principal)

- Roles: `FACULTY`, `PRINCIPAL` only (layout + login guard)
- `approveEvent(id, { sendToPrincipal, isPrincipal })` — direct approve or escalate
- `returnEventToCouncil(id, feedback)` — `DRAFT` + comment
- Pending queue: `app/(dashboard)/pending/page.tsx`

## Cross-app consistency

- Keep event types and `transformEvent` logic aligned between council-app and faculty `lib/api.ts`
- Backend is shared — API changes in `backend/` may require updates in all three frontends
- Match each app's existing Tailwind tokens and component patterns
